This is a must have for any phone owner. I do not normally write reviews for a phone game,but this one really is showing how innovative an Indie developer can be. The art in the game is great and original, if one were to sum it up in a word Amazing!!! I would give it easily a 10/10 for just how original the artwork is. It is on par with the great console games like Borderlands in art direction. An overall great experience that has great gameplay that will keep you wanting to come back for more, you will be wasting hours on this until you complete every level and collect all the apples. Overall an awesome game that any Android owner should own.

Technically, this is a well-implemented, cute game with easy-to-learn gameplay. It's commendably easy and quick to recover from failure, which adds to its addictiveness.  Where the game falls down for me is that all you do is essentially memorize and repeat complex chains of perfectly-timed moves. The only way to do this is by failing each level repeatedly. On many levels, particularly the later ones, it is simply impossible to complete the first time, because you can't see and prepare for what's coming at you off-screen. In a few places, it's even a matter of just being supremely lucky on the timing.  This really hearkens back to the days of early video games, where the only way to be challenging was for the game to cheat. It's 2012, folks. We're better than that now.
